cs.DC, cs.CC, cs.NI, cs.SE, cs.DS

This paper discusses the monitoring and benchmarking of cloud applications, which involves distributed systems, networking, and software engineering. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses the use of hardware and software platforms, which falls under cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The monitoring and benchmarking of QoS involves networking, which falls under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the development and validation of a framework, which falls under cs.SE (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper discusses the use of data processing frameworks, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
